I went to school
for computer science

00:43:20.010 --> 00:43:22.855
originally and
switched to theater.

00:43:22.855 --> 00:43:24.730
Because they didn't take
back my scholarship.

00:43:24.730 --> 00:43:26.990
CHRIS JACKSON: That's
just too meta, I can't.

00:43:26.990 --> 00:43:29.760
JOEL KARIE: So
like that's spooky.

00:43:29.760 --> 00:43:33.182
But also, as a
young person I had

00:43:33.182 --> 00:43:35.640
immigrant parents who they're
like, you will do everything.

00:43:35.640 --> 00:43:37.410
You play instruments,
you will speak languages,

00:43:37.410 --> 00:43:39.034
you will do all these
different things.

00:43:39.034 --> 00:43:42.360
Because we're in America
and we're going to do well!

00:43:42.360 --> 00:43:45.810
So all those classes and things
that I took, I never really

00:43:45.810 --> 00:43:47.010
thought would be important.

00:43:47.010 --> 00:43:48.385
But the great
thing about theater

00:43:48.385 --> 00:43:51.120
is it's so collaborative.

00:43:51.120 --> 00:43:54.480
It's only a matter of time
before a show comes along

00:43:54.480 --> 00:43:58.620
that is going to need
your expertise in coding,

00:43:58.620 --> 00:44:01.710
or in playing the saxophone.

00:44:01.710 --> 00:44:04.332
I mean, when "Lion
King" started,

00:44:04.332 --> 00:44:05.790
we didn't think
that there would be

00:44:05.790 --> 00:44:11.160
a hugely successful rap-based
musical about the founding

00:44:11.160 --> 00:44:12.335
of this nation.

00:44:12.335 --> 00:44:13.210
You know what I mean?

00:44:13.210 --> 00:44:14.779
Like it's only a matter of time.

00:44:14.779 --> 00:44:16.320
So you have to be
when you're young--

00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:18.319
or when you're not--
throughout your whole life,

00:44:18.319 --> 00:44:21.090
you have to be a sponge and
constantly absorb and take

00:44:21.090 --> 00:44:24.180
every opportunity it has given
to you to grow and to learn.

00:44:24.180 --> 00:44:26.700
Because it will be applicable
to art at some point.

00:44:26.700 --> 00:44:28.200
Because that's what
makes art great.

00:44:28.200 --> 00:44:29.700
That's what keeps it changing.

00:44:29.700 --> 00:44:32.220
CHRIS JACKSON: Broadway is the
pinnacle of commerce and art

00:44:32.220 --> 00:44:36.120
sort of crashing
into one another.

00:44:36.120 --> 00:44:38.540
So it's a very specific thing.

00:44:38.540 --> 00:44:42.260
I tell anyone, no matter what
line of work that you're in,

00:44:42.260 --> 00:44:43.920
pursue your passion.

00:44:43.920 --> 00:44:46.264
So if performing is something
that you care about,

00:44:46.264 --> 00:44:48.680
and that's something that you
just wake up in the morning,

00:44:48.680 --> 00:44:52.670
(SINGING) I got to do this,
go to work, pay your bills,

00:44:52.670 --> 00:44:55.550
but there are lots of
places to be an artist.

00:44:55.550 --> 00:44:58.100
There's lots of different
ways to do that.

00:44:58.100 --> 00:45:01.790
There are lots of communities
that completely welcome that.

00:45:01.790 --> 00:45:03.590
And I know especially
in the Bay Area,

00:45:03.590 --> 00:45:05.240
there's 100 theaters out there.

00:45:05.240 --> 00:45:07.257
Get your life, man.

00:45:07.257 --> 00:45:08.090
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

